Name: University of California, Santa Barbara
Description: UCSB is a publis research univerity in Santa Barbara, California. This univerity is 1 one of the 10 campusues under the Univerity of Claifronia system. This beautiful campus is located along the cliffs next to the Pacific Ocean. It is one of the few campuses in the US that has its own beach.

Name: Mendenhall Glacier Caves, Alaska
Description: 13.6 miles of glacier thats located in Mendenhall Valley. This retreating glacier has formed the lake that is known as the Mendenhall Lake. This location is known as  one of the  "rivers of ice". This glacier was formed during the Little Ice Age that occured 3,000 years ago. You can go to this location where you can walk on the land that was once under ice decades ago. There is an annual snowfall of over 100 feet which is crucial inorder to prevent the melting of the glacier.

Name: Lake Tahoe, United States
Description: The Sierra Nevada Mounatins emcompass Lake Tahoe. The clear waters allow someone to be able to see up to 70 feet deep. This large freshwater lake has an average depth of 1,000 ft(300m) and a maximum depth of 1,645 ft(501m). This lake lies on the border of California and Nevada. This incredible location is known for its clear waters and the panoramic view of the surrounding mountains.

Name: Machu Picchu, Peru
Description: This historical site was built starting in 1450 to about 1460. This location is referred to as the "Lost City of the Incas".

Name: Venice, Italy
Description: This amazing city has no roads old canals and is the capital of the Veneto region. From the beginning the city was built on dirt and mud which over time squeezed out the water from the compacted soil.

Name: Cinque Terre, Italy
Description: Cinque Terre stands for five lands which represents the 5 towns that have incredible seaside views and colorful houses.
